    "instruction": "Filter the trace_anomaly_rows for the earliest anomaly timestamp (the minimum timestamp present in trace_anomaly_rows). Return all anomaly rows at that timestamp (limit to 50) with columns: timestamp, _dt, cmdb_id, trace_name, value, p95, direction (as before). Additionally add a derived column named 'implicated' defined as: if trace_name contains 'to_' then the substring after 'to_' up to the next '.' or end; else if it contains 'from_' then the substring after 'from_' up to the next '.' or end; else empty. Store this displayed result in kernel variable trace_earliest_rows and return it." 
